<subSubSection pageId="278" pageNumber="279" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="278" pageNumber="279">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="278" pageNumber="279">This species is native to South America and is adventive in North America where it is known from southeastern United States (Nichols 1985b: 380). The first inventoried specimen collected on this continent was found in Mobile, Alabama in 1948 (Nichols 1985b: 380).</paragraph>
